# Tailwind Configuration

## Tailwind Configuration
- Using Tailwind CSS v3.3.5 (not v4).
- Content paths configured in `tailwind.config.js` for all source directories.
- Custom theme extensions in config file, not CSS variables for design tokens.
- Use PostCSS with Tailwind; no CSS-in-JS libraries.

## Design System
- Dark theme default: `bg-[#0b0b10]` for main background, `bg-[#121218]` for cards.
- Accent color: `#00ffc6` (cyan-green) for primary actions.
- Text colors: `text-white` for primary, `text-white/60` for secondary, `text-white/40` for tertiary.
- Border colors: `border-white/10` for subtle dividers.

## Styling Patterns
- Use utility classes directly in JSX; avoid custom CSS when Tailwind covers it.
- Custom colors use arbitrary values: `bg-[#121218]`, `text-[#00ffc6]`.
- Gradients: `bg-gradient-to-br from-[#001229] via-[#014b8f] to-[#00b47f]`.
- Spacing: consistent use of `p-4`, `gap-3`, `mt-2` etc.
- Rounded corners: `rounded-lg` (8px), `rounded-xl` (12px), `rounded-2xl` (16px).

## Component Styling
- Card pattern: `rounded-2xl border border-white/10 p-4 bg-white/5 shadow-xl shadow-black/20 backdrop-blur-sm`.
- Button primary: `px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-white text-black font-medium`.
- Button secondary: `px-3 py-2 rounded-lg bg-white/10`.
- Input fields: `w-full bg-black border border-white/20 rounded px-3 py-2`.

## Do
- Use Tailwind utilities for all styling.
- Follow existing color palette and spacing scale.
- Use arbitrary values for custom colors from design system.
- Keep component styles co-located with components.

## Don't
- Write custom CSS for things Tailwind can do.
- Use inline styles except for dynamic values.
- Mix Tailwind v3 patterns with v4 syntax.
- Create one-off color values; use design system colors.

